</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-24_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Quickly assessing a patient’s level of consciousness is a pivotal first aid skill, directly impacting the emergency response and subsequent medical treatment. Studies suggest that early recognition of consciousness levels in an emergency can enhance the accuracy of diagnosis and improve patient outcomes. The AVPU scale is endorsed by numerous health authorities and organisations as a reliable, quick assessment tool.
